        <mxCell id="note-key" value="&lt;b&gt;Key observations from this sequence&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;• Developer sees only GitHub PR + Slack message — never interacts with pipeline nodes directly · Orchestrator is the single voice&lt;br&gt;• 2 LLM calls in total: Triage (llama-3.3-70b, ~30s, ~$0.0004) + Reporter (llama-3.3-70b, ~5s, ~$0.0001) · 5 of 7 nodes are zero-cost code&lt;br&gt;• DB updated at every status transition — auditable timeline with timestamp, outcome, cost per node&lt;br&gt;• If Triage API fails at step 16, deterministic fallback runs instead — graceful degradation, run continues&lt;br&gt;• If confidence &lt; 0.80 after step 17: SSE hitl_required fires → QA Manager reviews in ApprovalQueue → POST /runs/{id}/approve → continue to step 19&lt;/span&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#F0F8FF;strokeColor=#2B6CB0;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;align=left;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="1295" width="2120" height="90" as="geometry" /></mxCell>
